  "pipeline_flow": [
    "1. Caller invokes handle(AgentPrompt $prompt, Closure $next)",
    "2. $next($prompt) executes the next stage in the pipeline, returns AgentResponse",
    "3. AgentResponse::then(callback) is chained",
    "4. Inside callback: check $agent->currentConversation()",
    "5. If no conversation: ConversationStore::storeConversation() → returns conversationId → $agent->continue(conversationId, participant)",
    "6. ConversationStore::storeUserMessage(conversationId, userId, prompt)",
    "7. ConversationStore::storeAssistantMessage(conversationId, userId, prompt, response)",
    "8. AgentResponse::withinConversation(conversationId, participant) — sets conversation metadata on response"
  ],

  "title_generation_flow": [
    "generateTitle() calls TextProvider::textGateway() → TextGateway",
    "TextGateway::generateText(provider, cheapestModel, systemInstruction, [UserMessage(prompt truncated 500)])",
    "Returns TextResponse; extracts $response->text limited to 100 chars",
    "On any Throwable: falls back to Str::limit($prompt, 100, preserveWords: true)"
  ],

  "important_notes": "RememberConversation is a Laravel-style pipeline middleware (handle + Closure $next pattern). It does NOT implement a formal interface — relies on duck-typing by the pipeline runner. The Agent object using RemembersConversations trait supplies currentConversation(), conversationParticipant(), and continue(). ConversationStore is the persistence boundary. Title generation uses a separate TextProvider call with the cheapest model.",

